Let's consider the possible relative positions of the two shaded squares:
\begin{enumerate}
    \item Adjacent horizontally or vertically:
        \begin{itemize}
            \item Adjacent in the same row (e.g., top left two squares): This can be rotated to be in any row.
            \item Adjacent in the same column (e.g., top left and middle left): This can be rotated to be in any column.
        \end{itemize}
    \item Diagonally adjacent:
        \begin{itemize}
            \item Diagonally adjacent (e.g., top left and middle center): This can be rotated to be in any diagonal.
        \end{itemize}
    \item Separated by one square horizontally or vertically:
        \begin{itemize}
            \item Separated by one square in the same row (e.g., top left and top right): This can be rotated to be in any row.
            \item Separated by one square in the same column (e.g., top left and bottom left): This can be rotated to be in any column.
        \end{itemize}
    \item Separated by one square diagonally:
        \begin{itemize}
            \item Separated by one square diagonally (e.g., top left and bottom right): This can be rotated to be in any diagonal.
        \end{itemize}
    \item Separated by two squares horizontally or vertically:
        \begin{itemize}
            \item Separated by two squares in the same row (e.g., top left and bottom right): This can be rotated to be in any row.
            \item Separated by two squares in the same column (e.g., top left and bottom right): This can be rotated to be in any column.
        \end{itemize}
    \item Separated by two squares diagonally:
        \begin{itemize}
            \item Separated by two squares diagonally (e.g., top left and bottom right): This can be rotated to be in any diagonal.
        \end{itemize}
\end{enumerate}

Let's enumerate the distinct patterns:
\begin{enumerate}
    \item Two adjacent squares in a row or column (e.g., top left and top middle).
    \item Two squares separated by one square in a row or column (e.g., top left and top right).
